query:
INSERT INTO activity_spots (name, islandGuideId, spotType, slug, latitude, longitude, difficulty, description, waveHeight, bestSeason, bestTime, coralCoverage, marineLife, maxDepth, minDepth, published) VALUES
('Cokes', 1, 'surf_spot', 'cokes-thulusdhoo', 4.2333, 73.2667, 'beginner', 'Fast right-hand reef break with consistent waves. Perfect for beginners and intermediate surfers. Mellow and forgiving.', '2-4 feet', 'March to October', 'Morning (6am-10am)', 'Heavy coral - reef break', 'Reef fish, occasional turtles', 15, 2, 1),
('Pasta Point', 1, 'surf_spot', 'pasta-point-thulusdhoo', 4.2350, 73.2680, 'intermediate', 'Excellent left-hand reef break with long, peeling waves. Named after the Italian restaurant nearby. Great for intermediate surfers.', '3-5 feet', 'March to October', 'Early morning (5am-9am)', 'Moderate coral', 'Reef sharks, trevally, grouper', 20, 3, 1),
('Jails', 1, 'surf_spot', 'jails-thulusdhoo', 4.2300, 73.2650, 'advanced', 'Powerful right-hand reef break with hollow sections. Requires experience and good paddling fitness. Heavy water movement.', '4-6 feet', 'March to October', 'Morning (6am-11am)', 'Heavy coral - sharp reef', 'Reef sharks, barracuda', 25, 4, 1),
('Chickens', 1, 'surf_spot', 'chickens-thulusdhoo', 4.2320, 73.2700, 'beginner', 'Mellow right-hand reef break. Forgiving waves with plenty of shoulder. Ideal for learning and progression.', '2-4 feet', 'March to October', 'Morning (7am-12pm)', 'Light coral', 'Small reef fish', 12, 2, 1);
